1
00:00:05,635 --> 00:00:18,310

2
00:00:23,704 --> 00:00:28,253

3
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:37,884

4
00:00:43,660 --> 00:00:45,807

5
00:01:09,143 --> 00:01:11,934

6
00:01:41,641 --> 00:01:45,239
这是可追溯至15世纪初期的修道院帐目
This is the monastery's account dating to the early 15th Century.

7
00:01:45,275 --> 00:01:46,685
哦 跟我想的一样
Oh, precisely what I thought.

8
00:01:46,757 --> 00:01:50,114
但无疑这有着巨大的政治意义
But surely this has great political significance.

9
00:01:50,586 --> 00:01:53,125
所以格外的棘手
A matter of particular delicacy.

10
00:01:53,198 --> 00:01:54,930
很抱歉打扰你 先生
Sorry to disturb you, sir,

11
00:01:55,008 --> 00:01:56,846
但Hopkins警督想见你
but inspector Hopkins would like to see you.

12
00:01:56,921 --> 00:01:59,069
前途无量的Hopkins警督
The promising Inspector Hopkins.

13
00:01:59,150 --> 00:02:02,247
靠近火炉 暖和一下
Draw up to the fire and warm your toes.

14
00:02:02,317 --> 00:02:04,014
希望你不会在这样一个夜晚
I hope you have no designs

15
00:02:04,093 --> 00:02:06,241
给我们找事做 警督
upon us on such a night as this, inspector.

16
00:02:06,321 --> 00:02:08,018
这是我的哥哥 Mycroft
This is my brother, Mycroft.

17
00:02:08,095 --> 00:02:09,969
或许你们之前没见过?
Maybe you have not met before?

18
00:02:10,044 --> 00:02:12,334
是的 不然我会有印象的
I'm sure, I would have remembered.

19
00:02:12,412 --> 00:02:15,214
我能跟你握个手吗 先生
May I shake your hand, sir?

20
00:02:16,589 --> 00:02:18,135
可以 如果你坚持的话
Yes, if you must.

21
00:02:18,172 --> 00:02:21,815
Hudson夫人知道
Now Mrs. Hudson knows a prescription

22
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,451
一个柠檬茶的配方
containing hot water and a lemon.

23
00:02:24,526 --> 00:02:26,708
我会给你弄些的 警督
I'll bring some up for you, inspector.

24
00:02:26,789 --> 00:02:28,485
那对御寒很有效
It'll help keep out the chill.

25
00:02:28,562 --> 00:02:29,772
谢谢你 Hudson夫人
Thank you, Mrs. Hudson.

26
00:02:29,851 --> 00:02:30,881
华生医生在哪里
Where is Dr. Watson?

27
00:02:30,918 --> 00:02:31,889
哦 在他的诊所里
Oh, in his surgery.

28
00:02:31,926 --> 00:02:32,983
我听说 这糟糕的天气
This dreadful weather

29
00:02:33,021 --> 00:02:35,560
让他的诊所外排起了长队
has produced a queue into the street I'm told.

30
00:02:35,597 --> 00:02:37,575
他们在浪费时间
Well they're wasting their time.

31
00:02:37,789 --> 00:02:39,900
华生用来治疗所有小病的就是
Watson's only cure for any ailment

32
00:02:39,981 --> 00:02:42,864
维他命冲剂和苹果泥
is linus powder and a grated apple.

33
00:02:42,939 --> 00:02:45,016
福尔摩斯先生 你知道你那样说只是
Mr. Holmes, you know you only say that

34
00:02:45,098 --> 00:02:47,652
因为你想念医生
because you miss the doctor.

35
00:02:49,379 --> 00:02:50,732
雪茄?
Cigar?

36
00:02:50,806 --> 00:02:52,195
不 不用了 谢谢
No, no, thank you.

37
00:02:52,999 --> 00:02:54,387
一定是什么重要的事
It must be something important

38
00:02:54,461 --> 00:02:55,991
才让你在这暴风天气中出门
to bring you out in such a gale.

39
00:02:56,063 --> 00:02:57,379
确实是
It is indeed.

40
00:02:57,455 --> 00:03:00,184
你看过有关Yoxley案件的最新报道吗
Did you see anything of the  Yoxley case in the latest editions?

41
00:03:00,221 --> 00:03:02,393
今天我还没看过晚于15世纪的事情
I see nothing later then the 15th Century today.

42
00:03:02,467 --> 00:03:05,908
我们在研究一本500年前的手稿
We've been studying a 500-year-old palimpsest.

43
00:03:05,984 --> 00:03:07,086
手稿?
Palimpsest?

44
00:03:07,167 --> 00:03:09,528
别管什么15世纪了
Enough of the 15th Century,

45
00:03:09,603 --> 00:03:12,408
你给我们带来了20世纪的新闻
you bring us news in the 20th.

46
00:03:12,770 --> 00:03:15,409
只是一个短篇报道 但内容齐全
Well it's only a paragraph, and all wrong at that.

47
00:03:15,447 --> 00:03:16,716
你应该不会错过什么
So you've not missed anything.

48
00:03:16,753 --> 00:03:19,152
听到这个我就放心了 警督
I'm relieved to hear it, inspector.

49
00:03:19,189 --> 00:03:21,204
事情发生在Kent
It's down in Kent,

50
00:03:21,686 --> 00:03:23,775
距Chatham有7英里远
seven miles from Chatham

51
00:03:23,812 --> 00:03:26,537
离铁路有3英里
and three from the railway line.

52
00:03:26,625 --> 00:03:29,127
我在3:15接到报案
I was wired for at 3:15,

53
00:03:29,201 --> 00:03:31,348
在5:00到达Chatham
got to Chatham at 5:00,

54
00:03:31,428 --> 00:03:32,958
并展开调查
conducted my investigation,

55
00:03:33,029 --> 00:03:35,391
乘最后一列火车回到Charing Cross
was back at Charing Cross by the last train

56
00:03:35,466 --> 00:03:37,937
之后乘出租马车直接来到你这里
and straight to you by cab.

57
00:03:38,669 --> 00:03:41,065
那意味着你对你的案子没把握
Which means you're not quite certain of your case.

58
00:03:41,140 --> 00:03:43,952
那意味着我理不出一点头绪
It means I can make neither head nor tale of it.

59
00:03:44,029 --> 00:03:47,779
没有作案动机 福尔摩斯先生
There's no motive, Mr. Holmes.

60
00:03:47,859 --> 00:03:49,768
作案动机 警督 什么作案动机?
Motive, Inspector, what motive?

61
00:03:49,843 --> 00:03:50,743
一个人死了
A man is dead,

62
00:03:50,817 --> 00:03:52,514
那是毫无疑问的
there's no denying that.

63
00:03:52,591 --> 00:03:57,462
但我看不出到底为什么 会有人希望他受到伤害
But I can see no reason between heaven  and earth why anyone should wish him harm.

64
00:04:07,212 --> 00:04:09,229
跟我们讲讲
Tell us about it.

65
00:04:10,971 --> 00:04:12,237
几年前
A few years ago

66
00:04:12,274 --> 00:04:14,832
<i>Yoxley旧居被一个老人买了下来</i>
<i>Yoxley Old Place was taken by an elderly man</i>

67
00:04:14,905 --> 00:04:17,302
<i>他叫Coram教授</i>
<i>by the name of Professor Coram.</i>

68
00:04:17,377 --> 00:04:18,586
<i>是个残疾人</i>
<i>He's an invalid,</i>

69
00:04:18,664 --> 00:04:20,217
<i>有一半的时间待在床上</i>
<i>keeping his bed half the time</i>

70
00:04:20,299 --> 00:04:22,933
<i>而剩下的另一半时间 要么是在房子里拄着拐杖</i>
<i>and the other half-hobbling about the house on a stick</i>

71
00:04:23,015 --> 00:04:25,269
<i>要么就坐在轮椅上</i>
<i>or being pushed about the grounds by the gardener</i>

72
00:04:25,348 --> 00:04:26,297
<i>被园丁推着</i>
<i>in a bath chair.</i>

73
00:04:26,334 --> 00:04:29,060
-我们到了 -你挺笨的 是不是
-Here we are. -Quite stupid, aren't you.

74
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:31,879
别着急 小心点
Now just take it easy, be very careful.

75
00:04:35,329 --> 00:04:36,420
小心
Careful.

76
00:04:45,919 --> 00:04:48,659
我的秘书在哪里 Marker夫人
Now where's my secretary, Mrs. Marker?

77
00:04:50,132 --> 00:04:51,934
<i>教授正在写一本学术著作</i>
<i>The professor is writing a learned book</i>

78
00:04:52,010 --> 00:04:53,978
<i>在一年前他发现有必要</i>
<i>and found it necessary about a year ago</i>

79
00:04:54,016 --> 00:04:55,519
<i>请一个秘书</i>
<i>to take on a secretary,</i>

80
00:04:55,596 --> 00:04:57,613
<i>Willoughby Smith先生</i>
<i>Mr. Willoughby Smith,</i>

81
00:04:57,685 --> 00:05:00,301
<i>一个刚从大学毕业的年轻人</i>
<i>a young man straight from the university.</i>

82
00:05:01,340 --> 00:05:05,933
如果一个人能接受基督一性论的学说
And if one can accept the doctrines of Monophysitism

83
00:05:06,005 --> 00:05:09,376
那么他必然也会重新评价
then perforce one must also re-evaluate

84
00:05:09,451 --> 00:05:11,592
基督教的宗教体系
Christian theology.

85
00:05:13,279 --> 00:05:14,774
建议...
To suggest...

86
00:05:14,846 --> 00:05:15,980
是的
Yes.

87
00:05:18,362 --> 00:05:20,402
建议...
To suggest...

88
00:05:20,554 --> 00:05:22,179
或者争论
Or to argue.

89
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:24,063
我们当中谁在写这本书
Which one of us is writing this book,

90
00:05:24,140 --> 00:05:25,635
你还是我?
you, or me?

91
00:05:25,706 --> 00:05:28,376
当然是您
You are, of course.

92
00:05:28,456 --> 00:05:29,844
建议...
To suggest...

93
00:05:29,919 --> 00:05:31,472
<i>刚开始 Smith看起来</i>
<i>From the first it appears that Smith</i>

94
00:05:31,554 --> 00:05:33,127
<i>是一个安静的受过良好教育的人</i>
<i>was a quiet, well-educated fellow</i>

95
00:05:33,127 --> 00:05:35,104
<i>并且几乎没有任何缺点</i>
<i>with hardly any weak spot in him at all.</i>

96
00:05:35,174 --> 00:05:37,084
<i>但就是这个年轻人</i>
<i>And yet this is the lad</i>

97
00:05:37,158 --> 00:05:38,546
<i>今天早晨死在了</i>
<i>who met his death this morning</i>

98
00:05:38,620 --> 00:05:40,174
<i>教授的书房里</i>
<i>in the professor's study</i>

99
00:05:40,257 --> 00:05:45,086
<i>就目前情况看来只能是谋杀</i>
<i>under circumstances that can point only to murder.</i>

100
00:05:45,164 --> 00:05:47,074
谋杀?
Murder?

101
00:05:47,148 --> 00:05:50,862
你是不是说Willoughby Smith被谋杀了 警督
Willoughby Smith was murdered you say, Inspector?

102
00:05:50,943 --> 00:05:52,567
请继续
Do go on.

103
00:05:52,648 --> 00:05:54,558
你的热柠檬茶 警督
Your hot lemon drink, inspector.

104
00:05:54,632 --> 00:05:56,400
谢谢 Hudson夫人
Thank you Mrs. Hudson,

105
00:05:56,477 --> 00:05:58,910
一个在世上没有任何敌人的人
a man without a single enemy in the world.

106
00:05:58,984 --> 00:06:01,262
Hudson夫人 你又在妨碍我们
Mrs. Hudson, you're under foot again.

107
00:06:01,299 --> 00:06:03,464
你说几乎没有任何缺点
When you say hardly any weak spots,

108
00:06:03,543 --> 00:06:04,967
那究竟是什么意思
what exactly do you mean?

109
00:06:05,041 --> 00:06:08,720
我们总会有这样那样的陋习
We all have vices of some kind or another.

110
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,638
Willoughby Smith没有前科
Willoughby Smith has nothing against him,

111
00:06:10,714 --> 00:06:13,110
当他在Uppingham上高中
either as a boy at Uppingham

112
00:06:13,185 --> 00:06:15,689
或是之后在剑桥上大学
or later as a young man at Cambridge.

113
00:06:15,762 --> 00:06:17,945
但我了解到他喜欢喝酒
Although I gathered that he was fond of a drink or two.

114
00:06:18,024 --> 00:06:19,483
那并不是件坏事
Well nothing wrong with that.

115
00:06:19,556 --> 00:06:21,501
他也有点好色
He also had a bit of an eye for the ladies.

116
00:06:21,574 --> 00:06:22,890
萝卜青菜各有所爱
Each to his own.

117
00:06:22,966 --> 00:06:25,220
也许他隐瞒了一个可怕的秘密
Perhaps he was hiding a terrible secret.

118
00:06:25,299 --> 00:06:26,924
Smith不认识邻里的任何人
Smith knew no one in the neighborhood

119
00:06:27,005 --> 00:06:29,295
跟他的雇主过着一样的生活
and lived very much as his employer did.

120
00:06:29,372 --> 00:06:30,902
教授埋首于他的创作
The professor was buried in his work

121
00:06:30,974 --> 00:06:32,218
也没有别的事可做
and existed for nothing else.

122
00:06:32,297 --> 00:06:34,550
跟你志趣相投啊 夏洛克
A man after your own heart, Sherlock.

123
00:06:34,627 --> 00:06:37,546
除了你提过的那三个人
Apart from the three people you have mentioned,

124
00:06:37,622 --> 00:06:39,390
房子里还有别的人吗
who else can be found in the house?

125
00:06:39,466 --> 00:06:41,933
一个上了年纪的女管家 Marker夫人
An elderly housekeeper, Mrs. Marker,

126
00:06:42,007 --> 00:06:44,567
和一个年轻的女仆 Susan Tarlton
and a young maid, Susan Tarlton.

127
00:06:45,940 --> 00:06:47,470
那谁发现了尸体
So who found the body?

128
00:06:47,542 --> 00:06:49,167
女仆 福尔摩斯先生
The maid, Mr. Holmes.

129
00:06:49,248 --> 00:06:51,208
她说当她听见惨叫时
She said she was working in an upstairs room

130
00:06:51,245 --> 00:06:52,968
她正在楼上的房间里工作
when she heard a cry.

131
00:06:53,041 --> 00:06:55,094
<i>她说当她到达书房时</i>
<i>She said by the time she got to the study</i>

132
00:06:55,165 --> 00:06:58,227
<i>Smith躺在了地上 受了致命伤</i>
<i>Smith was lying on the floor fatally wounded.</i>

133
00:06:58,299 --> 00:06:59,889
<i>她说</i>
<i>She says.</i>

134
00:07:38,815 --> 00:07:41,475
教授
Professor.

135
00:07:41,512 --> 00:07:46,591
教授...教授...
The professor.

136
00:07:47,902 --> 00:07:50,440
是她
It was she.

137
00:07:58,866 --> 00:08:00,420
<i>女仆发誓说</i>
<i>The maid is prepared to swear</i>

138
00:08:00,502 --> 00:08:02,935
<i>这是他的原话</i>
<i>that those were his exact words.</i>

139
00:08:05,619 --> 00:08:09,500
教授 是她
The professor, it was she.

140
00:08:10,632 --> 00:08:12,743
我画了一张草图
I've drawn up a rough plan

141
00:08:12,824 --> 00:08:16,890
应该会让你对教授书房的位置 有个大体的了解
that should give you a general idea of the position of the professor's study

142
00:08:16,966 --> 00:08:22,387
还包括在我看来 这个案件里各种重要的地方
and also the various points of the case which seem to me to be essential.

143
00:08:22,466 --> 00:08:23,342
正如你所见
As you can see

144
00:08:23,379 --> 00:08:25,936
从书房出来有两个走廊
there are two corridors which lead from the study.

145
00:08:26,017 --> 00:08:28,972
一个直接通向房子的后门
One goes directly to a door at the back of the house

146
00:08:29,046 --> 00:08:32,557
而另一个通向教授的卧室
and the other straight to the professor's ground floor bedroom.

147
00:08:33,083 --> 00:08:36,037
两个成90度的走廊
Two corridors with a 90-degree angle

148
00:08:36,111 --> 00:08:39,517
在书房外会合
joined at one end outside the study.

149
00:08:39,593 --> 00:08:42,441
现在假设凶手进了房子
Now assuming the assassin entered the house,

150
00:08:42,516 --> 00:08:43,974
他怎么进来的呢
how did he get in?

151
00:08:44,049 --> 00:08:47,525
毫无疑问从花园的小径和后门走
Undoubtedly by the garden path and the back door,

152
00:08:47,598 --> 00:08:49,330
那将直接
which gives direct access

153
00:08:49,408 --> 00:08:51,247
经过走廊到达书房
via the corridor to the study.

154
00:08:51,323 --> 00:08:52,462
完全正确
Exactly.

155
00:08:52,541 --> 00:08:54,830
而且他必须从同一条路逃走
And he must have made his escape along the same line.

156
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:57,135
因为书房的其他两个出口
For of the two other exits from the study,

157
00:08:57,172 --> 00:08:58,412
一个被女仆堵住了
one was blocked by the maid

158
00:08:58,494 --> 00:08:59,810
那时她正从楼上下来
as she ran downstairs

159
00:08:59,886 --> 00:09:02,319
而另一条直接通向教授的卧室
and the other goes straight to the professor's bedroom.

160
00:09:02,393 --> 00:09:06,539
那凶手不能从书房的窗户逃走吗
Could not the assassin have made his escape from the study window?

161
00:09:06,575 --> 00:09:08,664
-被锁上了 先生 从里面 -我明白了
-Locked sir, from within. -I see.

162
00:09:08,702 --> 00:09:10,513
这对于把你的理论付诸实践
It was an excellent opportunity

163
00:09:10,549 --> 00:09:12,615
是个绝佳的机会
to put your theories into practice.

164
00:09:12,696 --> 00:09:16,243
我注意了一下那条
I directed my attention at once to the garden path,

165
00:09:16,315 --> 00:09:19,472
被最近雨水浸洗过的花园小道
which was saturated with recent rain.

166
00:09:19,553 --> 00:09:21,736
小道上没有发现脚印
No footmarks were to be found on the path

167
00:09:21,815 --> 00:09:23,547
但毫无疑问
but there could be no question

168
00:09:23,626 --> 00:09:28,491
有人沿着草地穿过那里
that someone had passed along the grass border, which lines it.

169
00:09:28,569 --> 00:09:29,885
他这么做
And that he'd done so

170
00:09:29,961 --> 00:09:31,871
是为了避免留下足迹
in order to avoid leaving a track.

171
00:09:31,945 --> 00:09:33,819
你在那里发现了脚印?
You found footmarks there?

172
00:09:33,895 --> 00:09:37,015
没有 但那些草被人踩过
Not exactly, but the grass was trodden down

173
00:09:37,096 --> 00:09:38,721
那只会是凶手干的
and it could only have been the murderer

174
00:09:38,802 --> 00:09:40,427
因为那天早晨包括园丁在内
since neither the gardener nor anyone else

175
00:09:40,508 --> 00:09:42,347
没有人会出现在那个地方
had been in the area that morning

176
00:09:42,422 --> 00:09:45,613
而雨是从夜里才开始的
and the rain had only begun during the night.

177
00:09:45,695 --> 00:09:47,568
好极了 警督
Bravo, inspector.

178
00:09:47,643 --> 00:09:51,246
我知道你会赞赏我的分析的 福尔摩斯先生
I knew you'd appreciate my reasoning, Mr. Holmes.

179
00:09:54,814 --> 00:09:57,211
那些草上的足迹
These tracks in the grass,

180
00:09:57,286 --> 00:09:58,840
是来的时候留下的 还是走的时候
were they coming or going?

181
00:09:58,921 --> 00:10:00,274
无法判断
It was impossible to say.

