Thank you, Miss Tarlton,

371
00:21:03,043 --> 00:21:04,860
Mycroft 警督
Mycroft, inspector.

372
00:21:06,663 --> 00:21:09,296
或许他是因为跟爱人吵架而被害
Perhaps he was the victim of a lover's quarrel?

373
00:21:09,378 --> 00:21:11,586
那他死得真不值
How very tiresome for the man.

374
00:21:14,773 --> 00:21:16,054
快中午了
It's nearly midday.

375
00:21:16,132 --> 00:21:17,934
教授还待在他的卧室里吗
Will the professor still be in his room?

376
00:21:18,011 --> 00:21:20,550
是的 他从昨天早上开始还没离开过那里
Yes, he hasn't left it since yesterday morning.

377
00:21:20,621 --> 00:21:22,689
那你得跟我介绍介绍
Then you must introduce me.

378
00:21:26,816 --> 00:21:28,169
怎么了 福尔摩斯先生
What is it, Mr. Holmes?

379
00:21:28,244 --> 00:21:30,783
两条走廊都是铺的椰衣垫 (椰子壳纤维编成的垫子)
Both corridors are lined with coconut matting.

380
00:21:30,855 --> 00:21:33,917
我注意到了
I've noticed.

381
00:21:33,988 --> 00:21:35,429
谢谢你 先生
Thank you, sir.

382
00:21:36,876 --> 00:21:38,825
这跟案子有什么关系呢
What of it.

383
00:21:40,323 --> 00:21:43,206
那似乎对我很有启发性
It seems to me to be suggestive.

384
00:21:43,282 --> 00:21:45,160
不见得吧
Indeed.

385
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:56,814
请进
Come.

386
00:22:12,139 --> 00:22:14,465
关上门 Hopkins
Close the door, Hopkins.

387
00:22:14,541 --> 00:22:17,899
寒冷的空气对我的支气管炎没好处
The cold air won't help my bronchial condition.

388
00:22:20,214 --> 00:22:23,848
你们其中一个肯定是夏洛克 福尔摩斯
One of you gentlemen must be Sherlock Holmes.

389
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:27,535
这是我的哥哥 Mycroft
This is my brother, Mycroft.

390
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:33,083
你抽烟吗 福尔摩斯先生
Are you a smoker, Mr. Holmes?

391
00:22:33,163 --> 00:22:35,372
抽烟是我唯一的陋习
I have few other vices.

392
00:22:37,409 --> 00:22:40,506
啊 亚历山大烟草
Uh, Alexandrian.

393
00:22:40,577 --> 00:22:43,197
-是的 请抽一支 -谢谢
-Yes, Pray take a cigarette. -Thank you.

394
00:22:43,234 --> 00:22:46,452
它们是由lonides为我特别准备的
I have them especially prepared by lonides.

395
00:22:46,530 --> 00:22:49,023
每次给我送来1000支
Sends me 1,000 at a time.

396
00:22:49,418 --> 00:22:51,503
我很苦恼不得不每隔两周
I grieve to say that I have to arrange

397
00:22:51,540 --> 00:22:54,018
安排一次新的送货
a fresh supply every fortnight.

398
00:22:55,197 --> 00:22:56,822
你呢 先生
You sir?

399
00:22:56,903 --> 00:23:00,097
不 谢了 不 我更喜欢这个
No, thank you, no, I prefer this.

400
00:23:15,352 --> 00:23:17,485
烟草和工作
Tobacco and my work,

401
00:23:17,522 --> 00:23:19,587
我只剩下这些了
that's all there is left of me,

402
00:23:19,625 --> 00:23:22,125
烟草和工作
tobacco and my work.

403
00:23:22,348 --> 00:23:27,676
现在 只有烟草
Now, only tobacco.

404
00:23:27,779 --> 00:23:31,813
谁能预见如此可怕的灾难
Who could have foreseen such a terrible catastrophe?

405
00:23:31,886 --> 00:23:33,345
我向你保证 福尔摩斯先生
I assure you, Mr. Holmes,

406
00:23:33,418 --> 00:23:36,409
在仅仅几个月的训练后
that after, what, just a few months, training,

407
00:23:36,481 --> 00:23:39,329
他就成为了一个非常好的助手
he was an admirable assistant.

408
00:23:39,404 --> 00:23:42,632
对这个案子你有什么看法
What do you think of the matter, hey?

409
00:23:42,712 --> 00:23:46,189
我还没有理出头绪来
I have not yet made up my mind.

410
00:23:50,509 --> 00:23:52,454
我会对你很感激的
I would indeed be indebted to you

411
00:23:52,527 --> 00:23:53,986
如果你能在黑暗中
if you could throw a light

412
00:23:54,059 --> 00:23:56,004
给我们带来一丝曙光
on all that is dark to us,

413
00:23:56,079 --> 00:24:00,707
对于像我这样一个半瘫痪的可怜的
such a blow, paralyzing to a poor, old bookworm,

414
00:24:00,777 --> 00:24:02,759
病弱的老书呆子也算是一种慰藉
invalid, like myself.

415
00:24:02,831 --> 00:24:07,032
你不能继续写你的著作吗 教授
Could you not continue with your work, professor?

416
00:24:07,113 --> 00:24:08,322
哎呀 福尔摩斯先生
Alas Mr. Holmes,

417
00:24:08,401 --> 00:24:11,248
我似乎失去了思考的能力
I seem to have lost the faculty of thought.

418
00:24:11,324 --> 00:24:12,384
哦 天哪
Oh dear.

419
00:24:15,119 --> 00:24:18,002
我最伟大的作品
My magnum opus,

420
00:24:18,078 --> 00:24:20,022
对在叙利亚和埃及的
my analysis of documents

421
00:24:20,097 --> 00:24:21,756
埃及土人的修道院内
found in the Coptic monasteries

422
00:24:21,837 --> 00:24:25,837
找到的文件进行分析
of Syria and Egypt.

423
00:24:25,910 --> 00:24:31,692
我希望能够 在现有的宗教基础上深入研究
It is a work that I hoped to have cut deep at the very foundations of revealed religion.

424
00:24:32,071 --> 00:24:34,581
这真令人叹为观止
This looks impressive.

425
00:24:36,074 --> 00:24:37,569
但我的健康每况愈下
But with my enfeebled health,

426
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:39,011
我不知道
I don't know that I shall

427
00:24:39,049 --> 00:24:41,847
在没有助手的情况下
ever be able to complete it,

428
00:24:41,922 --> 00:24:44,438
还能不能把它写完
without my assistant.

429
00:24:50,868 --> 00:24:53,193
我不想用什么冗长的调查
I don't want to trouble you

430
00:24:53,269 --> 00:24:56,506
来打扰你
with a lengthy examination.

431
00:24:57,204 --> 00:24:58,603
简单地说
Simply,

432
00:25:01,310 --> 00:25:04,265
我只想问你 Willoughby Smith的遗言
to ask you what Willoughby Smith

433
00:25:04,339 --> 00:25:07,946
是什么意思
meant by his last words,

434
00:25:08,029 --> 00:25:10,622
"教授 是她"
"The professor, it was she?"

435
00:25:13,215 --> 00:25:14,762
Susan
Susan,

436
00:25:15,512 --> 00:25:19,050
一个乡村姑娘 福尔摩斯先生
a country girl, Mr. Holmes.

437
00:25:19,088 --> 00:25:21,116
你一定注意到了那个阶级
You must be aware of the incredible stupidity

438
00:25:21,186 --> 00:25:22,988
令人难以置信的愚蠢
of that class.

439
00:25:23,970 --> 00:25:27,936
设想一下 我那可怜的助手 低声说了一些不连贯的话
I fancy the poor fellow murmured some incoherent words

440
00:25:27,974 --> 00:25:31,159
而她硬把它们组成毫无意义的信息
and she twisted them into a meaningless message.

441
00:25:36,363 --> 00:25:40,270
对于这场悲剧 你对自己的名字 出现在遗言里就没有任何解释?
You have no explanation yourself for the tragedy?

442
00:25:41,445 --> 00:25:43,117
可能吧
Possibly.

443
00:25:43,568 --> 00:25:47,446
下面的话我只想在我们之间说
I breathe this only among ourselves.

444
00:25:48,094 --> 00:25:49,968
可能是自杀
Possibly suicide.

445
00:25:50,042 --> 00:25:51,828
自杀
Suicide.

446
00:25:52,758 --> 00:25:56,021
年轻人有他们所不为人知的麻烦 福尔摩斯先生
Young men have their hidden troubles, Mr. Holmes,

447
00:25:56,100 --> 00:25:58,362
或许是感情破裂的问题
an affair of the heart perhaps,

448
00:25:58,571 --> 00:26:01,016
这些是我们不可能知道的
which we will never know.

449
00:26:02,539 --> 00:26:05,601
这是一种比谋杀更有可能的假设
It's a more probable supposition than murder.

450
00:26:05,672 --> 00:26:07,591
那夹鼻眼镜又作何解释
And what of the pince-nez?

451
00:26:09,884 --> 00:26:14,713
一把扇子 一只手套 一副眼镜
A fan, a glove, eye-glasses

452
00:26:14,792 --> 00:26:18,613
谁知道人临死前会带着什么
who knows what article may be carried as a token

453
00:26:18,691 --> 00:26:24,850
纪念品或是值钱的东西吧
or treasured when a man puts an end to his life.

454
00:26:24,921 --> 00:26:27,297
我得离开这里了
I must get out of here.

455
00:26:28,542 --> 00:26:30,975
也许我说话像个小孩子
Possibly I speak as a child,

456
00:26:31,048 --> 00:26:35,703
但在我看来 Willoughby Smith是自杀的
seems to me Willoughby Smith met his fate by his own hand.

457
00:26:35,740 --> 00:26:38,912
Willoughby Smith是被谋杀的 他没有自杀
Willoughby Smith was murdered. He did not commit suicide.

458
00:26:38,985 --> 00:26:40,266
下午好 先生
Good afternoon, sir.

459
00:26:40,342 --> 00:26:41,552
是的 我同意
Yes, I agree.

460
00:26:41,908 --> 00:26:44,540
那教授所说的对这个案子毫无帮助
So the professor's theory has no bearing on the case.

461
00:26:56,145 --> 00:26:57,426
能麻烦你
Will you be good enough

462
00:26:57,503 --> 00:26:59,793
替我安排马车
to arrange carriage and escort for me

463
00:26:59,870 --> 00:27:01,886
和火车的行程吗
as far as the railway station?

464
00:27:01,959 --> 00:27:03,203
当然 先生
Of course, sir.

465
00:27:03,282 --> 00:27:05,655
我得回去一趟 所以我会带你一起走
I have to get back to town so I'll take you there myself.

466
00:27:05,692 --> 00:27:07,590
你真是太好了
You're very kind.

467
00:27:10,103 --> 00:27:11,977
我认为你会觉得
I think you might find

468
00:27:12,053 --> 00:27:14,414
这比亚历山大烟草
this more beneficial

469
00:27:14,490 --> 00:27:17,687
更有用
than Alexandrian tobacco.

470
00:27:19,780 --> 00:27:22,353
你还记得在我们年轻的时候
Do you remember what papa used to tell us

471
00:27:22,426 --> 00:27:23,921
父亲是怎么教导我们的?
when we were young?

472
00:27:23,958 --> 00:27:25,725
除去不可能的
Eliminate the impossible

473
00:27:25,803 --> 00:27:27,191
不管剩下什么
and whatever remains,

474
00:27:27,264 --> 00:27:28,996
也不管剩下的如何不大可能
however improbable,

475
00:27:29,074 --> 00:27:32,033
那一定就是真相
must be the truth.

476
00:27:32,695 --> 00:27:35,490
我忘了他的原话
I forget his exact words

477
00:27:35,526 --> 00:27:37,701
但我说的基本接近
but those are near enough.

478
00:27:37,881 --> 00:27:39,888
回头见
See you in London.

479
00:27:39,925 --> 00:27:41,991
Ionides (一个俄国人名)
Ionides.

480
00:27:47,558 --> 00:27:49,218
我没注意到一些事
I'm overlooking something,

481
00:27:49,298 --> 00:27:51,904
但它就在我眼前
and it's staring me in the face.

482
00:27:56,852 --> 00:27:58,739
哦 谢谢你
Oh, thank you my dear.

483
00:28:01,795 --> 00:28:03,110
坏消息 先生
Bad news I'm afraid, sir.

484
00:28:03,187 --> 00:28:04,575
直到今天很晚才有
There isn't another train for Charing Cross

485
00:28:04,649 --> 00:28:05,965
去Charing Cross的火车
till late this evening.

486
00:28:06,042 --> 00:28:07,810
你应该在把我拽到这里来之前
You should double-check the railway timetable

487
00:28:07,886 --> 00:28:10,105
仔细检查火车时刻表
before dragging me to this wretched place.

488
00:28:10,184 --> 00:28:11,809
我知道 先生 抱歉 先生
I know sir and I'm sorry sir.

489
00:28:11,890 --> 00:28:14,179
等一下 警督
Just a minute, inspector.

490
00:28:14,256 --> 00:28:16,404
我们可以等会儿回伦敦
London can wait.

491
00:28:16,485 --> 00:28:20,829
我认为我们应该推迟我们行程
I think we should postpone our trip for a little while

492
00:28:20,905 --> 00:28:23,124
去参加一个政治集会
to attend a political meeting.

493
00:28:23,203 --> 00:28:26,587
我们总是听到改革改革
We hear of reform after reform.

494
00:28:27,832 --> 00:28:29,600
我们不该支持这些女性 福尔摩斯先生
We shouldn't encourage these women, Mr. Holmes.

495
00:28:29,677 --> 00:28:32,054
她们是闹事者 比罪犯好不到哪儿去
They're troublemakers, no better then criminals.

496
00:28:32,092 --> 00:28:35,618
组织者 Abigail Grosby小姐
Organizer, Miss Abigail Grosby

497
00:28:35,699 --> 00:28:38,856
7点半
meeting held in the church hall

498
00:28:38,936 --> 00:28:40,810
在教堂集会
at half past 7:00.

499
00:28:40,886 --> 00:28:43,105
想想吧 警督
Think back inspector,

500
00:28:43,183 --> 00:28:45,615
Willoughby Smith的日记
Willoughby Smith's diaries,

501
00:28:45,688 --> 00:28:47,705
修道院 7:30
Abbey 7:30.

502
00:28:47,777 --> 00:28:49,272
你能小声点吗
Do you mind?

503
00:28:49,344 --> 00:28:53,094
感谢你们如此的敏锐
Thank you gentlemen for your sensitivity.

504
00:28:53,172 --> 00:28:56,269
我们总是听到改革改革
We hear of reform after reform

505
00:28:56,340 --> 00:28:58,388
但仍然没有采取任何措施
and yet still nothing is done

506
00:28:58,424 --> 00:29:01,601
来提高女性的社会地位
to improve the position of women in society.

507
00:29:01,702 --> 00:29:03,470
我们国家的命运
The fate of our country

508
00:29:03,546 --> 00:29:06,322
仍然只是由男性来决定
is still being decided by men alone

509
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:07,645
而女性
and yet women,

510
00:29:07,723 --> 00:29:10,049
在法律上
who are subjected daily and equally

511
00:29:10,125 --> 00:29:11,655
具有同等的地位
to the laws of the land,

512
00:29:11,727 --> 00:29:14,789
却不允许投票
are not permitted to vote.

513
00:29:19,907 --> 00:29:24,180
那一定是Abigail Grosby小姐
That must be Miss Abigail Grosby,

514
00:29:24,257 --> 00:29:26,161
真可怕
formidable.

515
00:29:26,198 --> 00:29:27,866
女性选举权
Votes for women indeed,

516
00:29:27,947 --> 00:29:29,371
接下来是什么
whatever next,

517
00:29:29,444 --> 00:29:31,141
女警察
women police,

518
00:29:31,220 --> 00:29:33,332
女政治家?
women politicians?

519
00:29:33,413 --> 00:29:35,072
我再次警告你
I'm not going to tell you again.

520
00:29:35,152 --> 00:29:37,514
女权解放运动
The struggle for female enfranchisement

521
00:29:37,589 --> 00:29:39,811
-至今都是以和平的方式进行 -上帝禁止这些
-has so far beena peaceful one. -God forbid.

522
00:29:39,848 --> 00:29:42,149
时机成熟了 我们必须扪心自问
The time has come and we must ask ourselves

523
00:29:42,186 --> 00:29:45,651
这个国家还会像这样持续多久
how much longer the state of affairs can continue?

524
00:29:45,689 --> 00:29:48,070
我们还应该忍受
How much longer we should allow ourselves

525
00:29:48,107 --> 00:29:50,495
二等公民的待遇多久
to be treated like second-class citizens?

526
00:29:50,573 --> 00:29:52,270
你告诉他们吧 Abigail
You tell them Abigail.

527
00:29:52,348 --> 00:29:53,320
扯淡
Poppycock.

528
00:29:53,392 --> 00:29:54,672
我想给你们读一封
I'd like to read you a letter

529
00:29:54,751 --> 00:29:55,960
我两天前收到的
which I received two days ago

530
00:29:56,037 --> 00:29:57,911
来自Garrett Fawcett夫人的信
from Mrs. Garrett Fawcett,

531
00:29:57,987 --> 00:30:00,004
她敦促我们继续斗争
urging us to continue the fight

532
00:30:00,076 --> 00:30:03,050
直到实现目标
until we achieve our aims.

533
00:30:05,507 --> 00:30:08,791
那应该会让你感兴趣的 警督
That should interest you, inspector.

534
00:30:12,189 --> 00:30:14,515
哦 哦 哦
Well, well, well.

535
00:30:28,027 --> 00:30:30,044
Mycroft
Mycroft.

536
00:30:30,116 --> 00:30:31,626
在各个领域
On every side,

537
00:30:31,663 --> 00:30:33,386
那些有能力帮助的人
those in a position to help,

538
00:30:33,458 --> 00:30:35,535
全都装聋作哑
are stricken by deafness.

539
00:30:35,616 --> 00:30:36,860
我们被告知这个国家
We're told that the country

540
00:30:36,938 --> 00:30:40,243
有比女性选举权更重要的事需要担心
has more important things to worry about than votes for women.

541
00:30:40,315 --> 00:30:41,489
那告诉我
Yet tell me,

542
00:30:41,568 --> 00:30:45,788
还有什么比占总人口数一半的人的权利更重要
what can be more important than the rights of half of the population?

543
00:30:45,825 --> 00:30:49,010
已故的的女王不也是个女人吗
Was the late queen not also a woman?

544
00:30:57,059 --> 00:31:01,859
我已经忍了这些犯罪课堂一天了 警督
I have had quite enough of the criminal classes for one day, inspector.

545
00:31:01,896 --> 00:31:04,363
你给我约的那辆马车在哪里
Where's that carriage you promised me?

546
00:31:15,889 --> 00:31:20,360
我真的一无所知 先生
I don't know nothing about nothing, sir, honest.

547
00:31:22,155 --> 00:31:24,748
那你干吗哭呢 Tarlton小姐
Then why are you crying Miss Tarlton?

548
00:31:25,394 --> 00:31:28,737
因为我不想惹上麻烦
Cause I don't want to be in no trouble.

549
00:31:28,774 --> 00:31:31,473
否则我会丢了工作
I'll lose my situation if I do.

550
00:31:31,553 --> 00:31:33,048
我再问你一次
I'll ask you one more time,

551
00:31:33,121 --> 00:31:35,174
Willoughby Smith是不是认识
was Willoughby Smith acquainted with

552
00:31:35,244 --> 00:31:37,841
那个叫Abigail Grosby的女教师
the schoolteacher Miss Abigail Grosby?

553
00:31:37,924 --> 00:31:39,348
我不知道
I don't know.

554
00:31:39,420 --> 00:31:41,532
你知道的 Tarlton小姐
You do know Miss Tarlton.

555
00:31:41,613 --> 00:31:44,568
撒谎是没用的
It's useless to lie.

556
00:31:44,642 --> 00:31:48,039
是的 他是认识
Yes, he was.

557
00:31:48,227 --> 00:31:50,935
他们互相认识
They knew each other all right.

558
