before justice would be done.

742
00:46:11,248 --> 00:46:13,232
我就在你手上 Anna
I'm in your hands, Anna.

743
00:46:17,826 --> 00:46:19,380
你总是对我那么好
You were always good to me.

744
00:46:20,750 --> 00:46:23,075
我的弟弟Alexis
My brother, Alexis,

745
00:46:23,151 --> 00:46:25,821
是个高尚无私的人
was noble, unselfish.

746
00:46:25,901 --> 00:46:27,669
他讨厌暴力
He hated violence

747
00:46:27,747 --> 00:46:29,337
还写了很多信
and wrote many letters

748
00:46:29,417 --> 00:46:31,706
试图劝阻我们不要继续下去
trying to dissuade us from such a course.

749
00:46:31,785 --> 00:46:34,881
这些信将会证明他是无辜的
These letters would have proved his innocence

750
00:46:34,952 --> 00:46:39,082
而你把它们从我这里偷走藏起来了
and you stole them from me and hid them.

751
00:46:39,164 --> 00:46:41,797
所以Alexis被流放到了西伯利亚
So Alexis was sent to Siberia

752
00:46:41,880 --> 00:46:45,486
至今还被关在那里
where he is even now.

753
00:46:51,242 --> 00:46:55,478
我的刑期一满
As soon as my time of imprisonment is over,

754
00:46:55,559 --> 00:46:57,327
我就决定取回
I determined to get the letters

755
00:46:57,404 --> 00:46:59,481
那些能释放我弟弟的信
that would procure my brother's release.

756
00:46:59,562 --> 00:47:03,038
我知道我的丈夫来到了英国
I knew that my husband had come to England

757
00:47:03,112 --> 00:47:05,165
在好几个月的调查后
and after many months of searching

758
00:47:05,236 --> 00:47:09,307
我确定了你在哪里
I determined where he was.

759
00:47:13,937 --> 00:47:18,316
所以最后我决定自己取回那些信件
So at last I determined to get the letters for myself.

760
00:47:18,393 --> 00:47:21,585
我才刚刚把它们从办公桌里拿出来
I had just removed them from the bureau

761
00:47:21,666 --> 00:47:25,451
这时那个年轻人抓住了我
when the young man seized me,

762
00:47:25,529 --> 00:47:29,386
那天早上早些时候我还遇到了他
the same young man I had met earlier that morning.

763
00:47:29,463 --> 00:47:31,646
我问他Coram教授住在哪里
I had asked him where Professor Coram lived

764
00:47:31,725 --> 00:47:34,787
但并不知道他就在他手下工作
not knowing that he worked for him.

765
00:47:34,858 --> 00:47:37,184
那他也一定跟教授谈到了你
And he must have told the professor about you.

766
00:47:37,260 --> 00:47:39,313
教授 是她
The professor, it was she.

767
00:47:39,383 --> 00:47:41,981
在他倒下后
When he had fallen,

768
00:47:42,064 --> 00:47:45,469
我跑了 但我走错了门
I ran but I went to the wrong door

769
00:47:45,544 --> 00:47:49,780
来到了他的房间
and found myself in his room.

770
00:47:49,861 --> 00:47:56,328
你 你说要把我供出去
You, you talked of giving me up.

771
00:47:56,405 --> 00:47:59,917
我告诉过你 如果你那么做
I showed you that if you did so

772
00:47:59,990 --> 00:48:02,873
我就毁了你的生活
your life was in my hands.

773
00:48:02,949 --> 00:48:05,867
如果你把我交给警察
If you gave me to the law

774
00:48:05,942 --> 00:48:10,108
我就把你交给组织
I could give you to the Brotherhood.

775
00:48:13,149 --> 00:48:18,609
那样我们的生命 就首次在婚后有了羁绊
That as our liveshad once been bound together in marriage.

776
00:48:18,682 --> 00:48:24,802
我们的命运也因此 永远交织在一起
So our destinies would forever be entwined.

777
00:48:24,878 --> 00:48:28,141
(俄语)
(Speaking Russian).

778
00:48:28,221 --> 00:48:30,583
结束了
It is finished.

779
00:48:30,657 --> 00:48:36,353
也绝不会开始
It never began.

780
00:48:36,435 --> 00:48:37,965
你的饭菜被送到了这里
You had your meals sent in here

781
00:48:38,036 --> 00:48:39,946
那样她就能跟你一起吃
so she could share your food.

782
00:48:40,021 --> 00:48:42,003
你们俩达成协议 当警察离开后
It was agreed that when the police left

783
00:48:42,075 --> 00:48:43,878
她就趁着夜色逃走
that she should slip away into the night

784
00:48:43,954 --> 00:48:45,792
并再也不相见
and never be seen again.

785
00:48:48,375 --> 00:48:51,675
这些信可以救我弟弟
These are the letters that will save my brother's life.

786
00:48:51,752 --> 00:48:55,430
把它们送去俄国大使馆
Take them to the Russian embassy.

787
00:49:07,693 --> 00:49:09,603
毒药
Poison.

788
00:49:43,999 --> 00:49:46,669
一封手写的信 福尔摩斯先生
A letter by hand, Mr. Holmes.

789
00:49:53,468 --> 00:49:55,484
谢谢你 Hudson夫人
Thank you Mrs. Hudson,

790
00:49:55,556 --> 00:49:57,014
睡个好觉
sleep well.

791
00:49:59,211 --> 00:50:02,474
<i>很明显 从眼镜的度数来看</i>
<i>It was clear to me from the strength of the spectacles</i>

792
00:50:02,553 --> 00:50:06,137
<i>如果被弄丢了 其佩带者必定跟瞎了一般</i>
<i>that the wearer must have been almost blind without them.</i>

793
00:50:06,207 --> 00:50:08,355
<i>因此我作出了</i>
<i>And I therefore considered the hypothesis</i>

794
00:50:08,435 --> 00:50:11,532
<i>她仍留在房子里的假设</i>
<i>that she remained within the house.</i>

795
00:50:11,603 --> 00:50:14,664
<i>你也许会说这很容易想到</i>
<i>You might say it was elementary.</i>

796
00:50:14,737 --> 00:50:16,290
<i>哦 对了</i>
<i>Oh, by the way,</i>

797
00:50:16,372 --> 00:50:19,184
<i>别跟华生提起鼻烟的事</i>
<i>don't mention the snuff to Watson.</i>

798
00:50:19,261 --> 00:50:21,967
<i>告诉他你故意掉下了 一些烟灰或什么东西</i>
<i>Tell him you dropped a cigarette ash or something.</i>

799
00:50:22,046 --> 00:50:23,991
<i>别让我惹上麻烦</i>
<i>Leave me out of it.</i>

800
00:50:24,065 --> 00:50:26,638
<i>但到底为什么 那位令人作呕的女人</i>
<i>But why on earth did the retched woman</i>

801
00:50:26,710 --> 00:50:30,258
<i>不得不自杀呢</i>
<i>feel compelled to take her own life?</i>

802
00:50:30,330 --> 00:50:32,329
她达到了她的目的
She'd achieved her purpose,

803
00:50:35,239 --> 00:50:38,762
毫无希望并且深处绝望之中
past hope and in despair,

804
00:50:40,425 --> 00:50:45,031
当然还有为爱殉情
and the death of love, of course.

805
00:50:47,630 --> 00:50:49,960
哦 教授
Oh, professor,

806
00:50:51,042 --> 00:50:55,510
望你罪有应得
be sure your sin will find you out.

807
00:50:57,697 --> 00:50:59,766

